{{Infobox language |name=Cauho |nativename= |states=[[Laos]] |region= |ethnicity= |speakers=? |date= |ref= |familycolor=Sino-Tibetan |fam2=([[Tibeto-Burman languages|Tibeto-Burman]]) |fam3=[[Lolo–Burmese languages|Lolo–Burmese]] |fam4=[[Loloish languages|Loloish]] |fam5=[[Southern Loloish languages|Southern]] |fam6=[[Bisoid languages|Bisoid]] |iso3=none |glotto=cauh1234 |glottorefname=Cauho }}
'''Cauho''' (autonym: ''cau˧ho˧'') is a [[Loloish language]] of northern [[Laos]]. It is divergent with the Bisoid (Phunoi) branch. Laos is in Asia.
