{{for|the clarinettist|Helmut Hödl}} '''Hodl''' ({{IPAc-en|ˈ|h|ɒ|d|əl}} {{respell|HOD|əl}}; often written '''HODL''') is slang in the [[cryptocurrency]] community for [[Buy and hold|holding]] the [[cryptocurrency]] rather than selling it.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/laurashin/2017/12/19/bitcoin-and-taxes-if-not-hodling-consider-donating|title=Bitcoin And Taxes: If Not HODLing, Consider Donating|last=Shin|first=Laura|work=Forbes|access-date=2017-12-22|language=en|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171222124446/https://www.forbes.com/sites/laurashin/2017/12/19/bitcoin-and-taxes-if-not-hodling-consider-donating/|archivedate=2017-12-22|df=}}</ref> It originated in a December 2013 post on the Bitcoin Forum message board by an apparently inebriated user who posted with a typo in the subject, "I AM HODLING."<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ftalphaville.ft.com/2017/12/22/2197074/the-hodl/|title=The HODL|last=Kaminska|first=Izabella|date=22 December 2017|website=Financial Times|language=en|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2018-11-21}}</ref> In 2017, [[Quartz (publication)|''Quartz'']] listed it as one of the essential slang terms in Bitcoin culture, and described it as a stance, "to stay invested in bitcoin and not to capitulate in the face of plunging prices."<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://qz.com/878728/buy-and-hodl-just-dont-get-rekt-the-slang-that-gets-you-taken-seriously-as-a-bitcoin-trader/|title=Buy and hodl, just don’t get #rekt: The slang that gets you taken seriously as a bitcoin trader|last=Wong|first=Joon Ian|work=Quartz|access-date=2017-12-22|language=en-US|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171222220057/https://qz.com/878728/buy-and-hodl-just-dont-get-rekt-the-slang-that-gets-you-taken-seriously-as-a-bitcoin-trader/|archivedate=2017-12-22|df=}}</ref> ''[[TheStreet.com]]'' referred to it as the "favorite mantra" of Bitcoin holders.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thestreet.com/story/14429339/1/bitcoin-fans-chant-hodl-as-price-plunges.html|title=As Bitcoin plunges, cryptocurrency fans chant 'HODL' for comfort|last=Akhtar|first=Tanzeel|date=2017-12-22|work=TheStreet|access-date=2017-12-22|language=en-US|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171223102117/https://www.thestreet.com/story/14429339/1/bitcoin-fans-chant-hodl-as-price-plunges.html|archivedate=2017-12-23|df=}}</ref> Though originally used in relation to holding [[Bitcoin]], it is now also used to describe holding other cryptocurrencies and tokens such as [[Ethereum]].
