{{Infobox language |name=Ipulo |nativename=Assumbo |altname= |states=[[Cameroon]] |ethnicity= |speakers=2,500 |date=1990 |ref = e18 |familycolor=Niger-Congo |fam2=[[Atlantic–Congo]] |fam3=[[Benue–Congo]] |fam4=[[Southern Bantoid]] |fam5=[[Tivoid languages|Tivoid]] |fam6=Central (B) |iso3=ass |glotto=ipul1238 |glottorefname=Ipulo }}
'''Ipulo''', or '''Assumbo''', is a [[Tivoid language]] of [[Cameroon]]. The rather divergent dialects are Olulu and Tinta/Etongo.
